00:06:48.060 --> 00:06:52.350
of a sales training company, it was a six
million dollar company compared to Proctor

00:06:52.350 --> 00:06:54.250
&amp; Gamble, so obviously very small.

00:06:54.250 --> 00:07:00.820
But I went to go work there because I really
believed in what they were doing.

00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:01.820
[pause]

00:07:01.820 --> 00:07:05.060
And so I went to go work, I was in business
development; I was in charge of business development.

00:07:05.060 --> 00:07:08.070
So the first year brought in a million dollars
worth of new business, second year brought

00:07:08.070 --> 00:07:10.199
in another million dollars worth of new business.

00:07:10.199 --> 00:07:13.320
And so a six million dollar company to bring
in a million dollars in new business two years

00:07:13.320 --> 00:07:15.712
in a row is like a big deal, especially a
training company where the margins are like

00:07:15.712 --> 00:07:16.770
40 percent.

00:07:16.770 --> 00:07:21.009
So I really liked it and I was a believer,
I believed in our programs, but there was

00:07:21.009 --> 00:07:28.259
always something missing 'cause we'd go and
we'd do these programs, the sales people would

00:07:28.259 --> 00:07:35.100
learn the skills, and inevitably there would
be one small group of people that would outperform

00:07:35.100 --> 00:07:39.150
the other people, there would always be those
outliers.

00:07:39.150 --> 00:07:40.900
And so I thought, "Something's missing.

00:07:40.900 --> 00:07:42.419
I wanna know what this is."

00:07:42.419 --> 00:07:46.710
So I started my own company, was doing a lot
of consulting work around the area of sales

00:07:46.710 --> 00:07:51.060
leadership, and what I wanna tell you about
it a project that I worked on and that had

00:07:51.060 --> 00:07:56.069
a profound experience on my life, the way
I think about sales, and the way I think about

00:07:56.069 --> 00:07:57.430
sales leadership.

00:07:57.430 --> 00:08:02.110
So I was hired, a group of consultants was
hired by this biotech company, this big biotech

00:08:02.110 --> 00:08:06.610
company had sales reps all over the world
and they wanted to know the same thing a lot

00:08:06.610 --> 00:08:09.710
of companies wanna know, same thing I wanna
know, what's the difference between the people

00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:14.830
that are good at the jobs and people who are
absolutely amazing in terms of sales numbers?

00:08:14.830 --> 00:08:19.660
So they hired this group of consultants and
we were gonna go out and we were gonna assess

00:08:19.660 --> 00:08:24.110
the salespeople; we were gonna ride with 'em,
follow their calls, do interviews, we did

00:08:24.110 --> 00:08:25.289
a whole host of things.

00:08:25.289 --> 00:08:31.710
And I should tell you this was a double blind
study in the sense that we didn't know who

00:08:31.710 --> 00:08:37.320
the top performers were, we were just looking
at the behavior and this was fascinating.

00:08:37.320 --> 00:08:41.510
So there's a lot of ways that you can look
at sales behavior and I'll show a couple of

00:08:41.510 --> 00:08:45.500
'em now and these are some pretty basic ways.

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:46.910
When you take a look at sales behavior –

00:08:46.910 --> 00:08:49.510
[sound of papers being shuffled]

00:08:49.510 --> 00:08:51.080
one thing a lot of people look at is –

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:53.530
[pause]

00:08:53.530 --> 00:08:58.550
customer knowledge and product knowledge,
and this is pretty easy to understand.

00:08:58.550 --> 00:08:59.550
Think about a salesperson --

00:08:59.550 --> 00:09:00.820
[pause]

00:09:00.820 --> 00:09:06.040
if you're low on the customer knowledge, low
on the product knowledge how do you think

00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:07.070
these people perform?

00:09:07.070 --> 00:09:08.070
They're terrible.

00:09:08.070 --> 00:09:09.820
This is not rocket science, they're terrible.

00:09:09.820 --> 00:09:14.540
Then we have salespeople who are high on customer
knowledge or high on product knowledge rather,

00:09:14.540 --> 00:09:15.540
but low on customer knowledge.

00:09:15.540 --> 00:09:18.360
What kinds of behavior do you think you see
from those salespeople?

