01:02:41.040 --> 01:02:47.109
In my experience what we usually do is we
say, "Here's what I recommend and here's why."

01:02:47.109 --> 01:02:48.109
[pause]

01:02:48.109 --> 01:02:51.059
Isn't that the way we usually do it?

01:02:51.059 --> 01:02:55.239
Well I'd like to suggest to you there's a
more powerful way to do that.

01:02:55.239 --> 01:02:58.549
It's a technique I call context and framing.

01:02:58.549 --> 01:03:02.960
If you show up for your customers and you
have a noble sales purpose and your purpose

01:03:02.960 --> 01:03:06.869
is to make a difference in their business,
you're probably gonna be pretty proactive

01:03:06.869 --> 01:03:10.369
about asking them questions 'cause you're
gonna need to know.

01:03:10.369 --> 01:03:14.609
How can I create success for you if I don't
know what success looks like for you?

01:03:14.609 --> 01:03:17.319
So when it comes time to present something
instead of saying, "Here's what I recommend

01:03:17.319 --> 01:03:21.749
and here's why," try this instead.

01:03:21.749 --> 01:03:25.799
Start with context: "You told me that one
of the things that you wanted to do was get

01:03:25.799 --> 01:03:27.140
more shoppers into the store.

01:03:27.140 --> 01:03:30.259
You appeal to younger people you wanna get
more shoppers into the store."

01:03:30.259 --> 01:03:33.740
Frame: there's a couple ways that you could
do this.

01:03:33.740 --> 01:03:36.099
You could do it this way, you could do this
way, you could do it this way.

01:03:36.099 --> 01:03:40.780
"As we look at this, this one is probably
going to be the most effective for you in

01:03:40.780 --> 01:03:43.799
helping you reach the objectives that you
set.

01:03:43.799 --> 01:03:46.339
And so that's why I recommend this."

01:03:46.339 --> 01:03:48.950
Did you hear the difference in that?

01:03:48.950 --> 01:03:52.170
It's very subtle but there is a distinct difference.

01:03:52.170 --> 01:03:59.989
So you provide the context first, then you
set up a frame, and then you deliver the message.

01:03:59.989 --> 01:04:01.229
[pause]

01:04:01.229 --> 01:04:05.670
It sounds backwards to us, but it's in order
for the customer.

01:04:05.670 --> 01:04:09.769
'Cause if I say I recommend this the customer's
brain is going, "And how does that fit with

01:04:09.769 --> 01:04:11.989
this and how does that fit with this and where
would that go with this?"

01:04:11.989 --> 01:04:13.339
The customer's brain is doing all that.

01:04:13.339 --> 01:04:17.239
Doing it this way I establish the context
first, "Okay we're all on the same place,

01:04:17.239 --> 01:04:18.239
here's what we wanna do.

01:04:18.239 --> 01:04:22.769
You said that you wanted to do this," and
I wanna be very clear on this I'm not talking

01:04:22.769 --> 01:04:24.099
about manipulating your customers.

01:04:24.099 --> 01:04:28.249
"Well you said and I'm gonna make you think,"
I'm not talking, I'm talking about doing this

01:04:28.249 --> 01:04:31.559
in a very authentic, intentional way.

01:04:31.559 --> 01:04:35.009
So if I wanna make the customers more successful
and I've uncovered what that looks like for

01:04:35.009 --> 01:04:38.220
them, I frame it up, "Here are the things
you wanted to accomplish in the next coming

01:04:38.220 --> 01:04:39.220
year.

01:04:39.220 --> 01:04:42.519
Now as we look at the advertising portion
of this there's this, there's this, there's

01:04:42.519 --> 01:04:43.519
this.

01:04:43.519 --> 01:04:46.150
Looking at these three things I think this
is the one that would give you the most bang

01:04:46.150 --> 01:04:50.170
for your buck and so what I recommend is this
is the way we need to implement."

01:04:50.170 --> 01:04:52.920
Can you hear the difference in that?

01:04:52.920 --> 01:04:55.799
That is pulling that purpose to the front
and center.

